<collectingCountry id="F33A7662FFF56362307C8E30FE57F6A9" box="[609,794,378,405]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF5636231318E30FE8CF6A9" author="Collin, J. E." box="[812,961,378,405]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="104 - 109" refId="ref4593" refString="Collin, J. E. 1939. Notes on Syrphidae (Diptera) III. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 75, 104 - 109." type="journal article" year="1939">Collin, 1939</bibRefCitation>
) actually refers to the locatity in 
<collectingCountry id="F33A7662FFF56362333F8ED0FC34F689" box="[290,377,410,437]" name="Austria" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Austria</collectingCountry>
(Speight, 2017).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF5636232C68EF0F985F5E9" blockId="2.[166,1225,314,725]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
Diagnosis. 
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636233678EF0FC9FF6E8" bold="true" box="[378,466,442,468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Female</emphasis>
differs from similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636230DE8EF1FEF7F6E9" authority="Collin, 1939" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[707,954,442,469]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636230DE8EF1FE68F6E8" box="[707,805,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">B. pilosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF5636231368EF0FEF7F6E9" author="Collin, J. E." box="[811,954,442,469]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="104 - 109" refId="ref4593" refString="Collin, J. E. 1939. Notes on Syrphidae (Diptera) III. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 75, 104 - 109." type="journal article" year="1939">Collin, 1939</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF5636231DA8EF0F96BF6E9" box="[967,1062,442,469]" captionStart="Figs 3–8" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetId="figure-317@2.[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 3–8. Females of Brachyopa plena (FIgs 3–5) and B. pilosa (from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">FIgs 6–8</figureCitation>
) by the larger and more ventral sensory pit on the basoflagellomere (distance between ventral edge of the pit and ventral edge of the basoflagellomere less than the diameter of the pit, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF5636236998EB0F9F2F529" box="[1156,1215,506,533]" captionStart="Figs 3–8" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetId="figure-317@2.[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 3–8. Females of Brachyopa plena (FIgs 3–5) and B. pilosa (from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">FIg. 5</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636232CD8D51FC7EF508" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[208,307,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636232CD8D51FC7EF508" box="[208,307,538,564]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distance between ventral edge of the pit and ventral edge of the basoflagellomere exceeds the diameter of the pit, as on 
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF5636230B98D70FF93F569" box="[676,734,570,597]" captionStart="Figs 3–8" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetId="figure-317@2.[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 3–8. Females of Brachyopa plena (FIgs 3–5) and B. pilosa (from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">FIg. 8</figureCitation>
), and numerous black hairs on the lateral margin of the second tergite (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636230038D11FFCDF548" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[542,640,602,628]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636230038D11FFCDF548" box="[542,640,602,628]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
all hairs pale, but the males have some black hairs and its quantity is rather variable) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF56362305F8D30FF9BF5A9" author="Collin, J. E." box="[578,726,634,661]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="104 - 109" refId="ref4593" refString="Collin, J. E. 1939. Notes on Syrphidae (Diptera) III. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 75, 104 - 109." type="journal article" year="1939">Collin, 1939</bibRefCitation>
; Speight, 2017). 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636231888D30F91AF5A8" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[917,1111,634,660]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plena">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636231888D30F91AF5A8" box="[917,1111,634,660]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Brachyopa plena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636232D88DD1FFC1F589" authority="Robineau-Desvoidy, 1844" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1844" box="[197,652,666,693]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636232D88DD1FC1AF588" box="[197,343,666,692]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
Robineau-Desvoidy, 
<quantity id="4CD59B17FFF5636230498DD0FFC1F589" box="[596,652,666,693]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.68376" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" unit="in" value="1844.0">1844</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in having basoflagellomere with ventral location of the sensory pit (distance between ventral edge of pit and ventral edge of antennal seg-
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF52667AFFF5636232BB8994FC1AF016" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" startId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" targetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF5636232BB8994FC1AF016" blockId="2.[166,1225,1758,1834]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
Figs 3–8. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636233688994FF58F1CF" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[373,533,1758,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plena">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636233688994FF58F1CF" box="[373,533,1758,1779]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Brachyopa plena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(FIgs 3–5) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF5636230B68995FFB0F1CF" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[683,765,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF5636230B68995FFB0F1CF" box="[683,765,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636331618FE5F99DF6D3" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
ment less than the diameter of the pit), differing by the rounded and smaller sensory pit (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636331C38E58F934F617" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1844" box="[990,1145,273,299]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636331C38E58F934F617" box="[990,1145,273,299]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, basoflagellomere with normally kidney-shaped or c-shaped and larger sensory pit), and notopleuron with black and pale pile (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF46363362F8EFFF99DF6F2" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1844" box="[1074,1232,436,462]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF46363362F8EFFF99DF6F2" box="[1074,1232,436,462]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually with pale pile only)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636331618EBFF99CF50C" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF4636331998EBFF955F52C" author="Collin, J. E." box="[900,1048,501,528]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" pagination="104 - 109" refId="ref4593" refString="Collin, J. E. 1939. Notes on Syrphidae (Diptera) III. The Entomologist's Monthly Magazine, 75, 104 - 109." type="journal article" year="1939">Collin, 1939</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC4B03FFF4636336398EBFFEB3F50C" author="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P." pageId="3" pageNumber="128" pagination="1 - 139" refId="ref5733" refString="Speight, M. C. D. &amp; Sarthou, J. - P. 2017. StN keys for the identiFIcation of the European species of various genera of Syrphidae 2017. Syrph the Net, the database of European Syrphidae (Diptera), 99, 1 - 139. Syrph the Net publications, Dublin." type="journal article" year="2017">Speight &amp; Sarthou, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens from
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636331618D7CF99DF56D" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" box="[892,1232,566,593]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<collectingCountry id="F33A7662FFF4636331618D7CFE91F56D" box="[892,988,566,593]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
have the notopleu-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636332B38D18F9FCF54E" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" box="[174,1201,594,626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Fig. 9. Male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636333218D18FCABF554" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[316,486,594,616]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636333218D18FCABF554" box="[316,486,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Brachyopa vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, dorsal view. ron with a few black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636331AC8D3DF99CF5AE" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" box="[945,1233,631,658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Additional features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636331618DD2F99CF58F" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" box="[892,1233,664,691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636331618DD2F92BF58E" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[892,1126,664,690]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plena">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636331618DD2F92BF58E" box="[892,1126,664,690]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Brachyopa plena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9236F2FFF4636332B38DF2FFFBF4E4" blockId="3.[174,1233,175,984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Zakarpattia have vertex as wide as width of the basoflagellomere (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF4636331808DF2FE96F5EF" box="[925,987,696,723]" captionStart="Figs 3–8" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetId="figure-317@2.[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 3–8. Females of Brachyopa plena (FIgs 3–5) and B. pilosa (from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIg. 4</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636336728DF3F99CF5EE" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[1135,1233,696,722]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636336728DF3F99CF5EE" box="[1135,1233,696,722]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingRegion id="49E9F810FFF4636332E08D93FCD8F5C8" box="[253,405,729,756]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Kyiv Region</collectingRegion>
), vertex is 1.33 times as wide as basoflagellomere width (
<figureCitation id="13162A77FFF4636336578D93F9C1F5C8" box="[1098,1164,729,756]" captionStart="Figs 3–8" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetId="figure-317@2.[277,1115,771,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 3–8. Females of Brachyopa plena (FIgs 3–5) and B. pilosa (from Kyiv Region) (FIgs 6–8): 3, 6 — habitus, dorsal view; 4, 7 — head, frontal view; 5, 8 — head, anterolateral view (arrow shows the sensory pit on the basoflagellomere)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454610" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454610/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">FIg. 7</figureCitation>
). The specimen from Zakarpattia has the postpronotum yellowish-brown, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF46363364B8DB0F9F4F42F" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1939" box="[1110,1209,761,787]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosa">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF46363364B8DB0F9F4F42F" box="[1110,1209,761,787]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. pilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is at least dorsally black. N o t e. Speight (2017) remarks that “…the shape of this pit varies, and occasional specimens may be found, among series of specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF4636331138C16FEEDF449" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1844" box="[782,928,859,885]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF4636331138C16FEEDF449" box="[782,928,859,885]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Western Europe, in which this pit is either oval or round, or of indeterminate shape”. We still admit that the specimen on hand can be an aberrant 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D4D71FFF46363306E8CD7FE48F48A" authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1844" box="[627,773,924,950]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachyopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B959EAE0FFF46363306E8CD7FE48F48A" box="[627,773,924,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">B. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with rounded sensory pit (that species has not been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F33A7662FFF4636333E78CF7FF17F4E4" box="[506,602,957,984]" name="Ukraine" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
either).
</paragraph>
